The '''Louisiade monarch''' ('''''Symposiachrus melanopterus''''') is a species of [[bird]] in the family [[Monarchidae]] [[Endemism|endemic]] to Papua New Guinea. It is found in the [[Louisiade Archipelago]]. Its natural [[habitat]]s are [[subtropical or tropical moist lowland forest]] and [[subtropical or tropical moist shrubland]]. It is threatened by [[habitat loss]].<!--- citation? --->

==Taxonomy and systematics==
The species was originally described as a species by [[George Robert Gray]] as ''Monarcha melanoptera'',<ref>{{Cite book |last=Zoological Society of London. |url=https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/100585 |title=Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London |last2=London |first2=Zoological Society of |last3=London |first3=Zoological Society of |date=1858 |publisher=Academic Press, [etc.] |volume=pt.26 (1858) |location=London}}</ref> later as a subspecies of the [[spectacled monarch]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.worldbirdnames.org/Archives/Master_IOC_list_v2.0.xls|title=IOC Bird List v2.0|date=2009|access-date=28 October 2016}}</ref>

